{{Quote|Clones can think creatively. You will find that they are immensely superior to droids.|[[Lama Su/Legends|Lama Su]] to [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]]|<ref name="Episode 2">{{Film|II}}</ref>}}
'''Kamino cloning chambers''', also called '''hatcheries''', were disk-shaped [[cloning tank]]s used to grow [[Cloning/Legends|clones]] on [[Kamino/Legends|Kamino]]. They were most notably used as the primary method of creating [[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett's]] clones, to be trained for service in the [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].

The cloning chamber was studded with cylinders that housed the developing clones. The genetic material from the host was originally taken and modified to the desired parameters, used to create artificial embryos in an egg lab. Then the new embryos were grown inside glass incubation wombs housed in the Kamino cloning chambers. There, the chamber provided the developing embryos with the nutrients they needed to develop in the form of a nutrient bath.

The components of the Kamino cloning chamber included the actual cloning chamber, diagnostics, DNA sequencing, energy supply, life support, and the fetal clones housed inside the chamber.

The [[Kaminoan/Legends|Kaminoans]] grew millions of clones for the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] in these chambers. Later, they would be used by the Kaminoans to grow their own renegade clone army to resist the fledgling [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]].

Several hatcheries were scattered throughout [[Tipoca City/Legends|Tipoca City]]. Kaminoans expected a survival rate of over ninety percent. Every so often, an entire batch would develop an issue.

